can i keep exercising with pain how i haven't been very active the last year and just started again but after the rd day my body is killing me i don't want to stop is it safe to keep going and what can i use for the pain i do full body work out for hr and then run skip for min take an anti inflammatory such as ibuprofen mg about a hour before you start your work out this will decrease inflammation in your muscles and joints and will slightly thin your blood and make it easier for blood to move through your system allowing for better oxygenation of your tissues which will decrease muscle cramping and soreness while your body starts to get back in shape you'll expect to have sore muscles but to have real bad pain isn't always pleasant but yes can be expected i suggest doing an exercise that has less impact on the joints but still works all the muscles until they get stronger swimming is the best exercise i can suggest for someone who is trying to get back in shape swim a few days a week if you can m w f and on tu th do a light jog or light weights with high repetition tu th is your time to let your muscles recover a little bit so don't over do it the trick is to get to do this as regularly as you can until your muscles have gotten stronger to do the higher impact stuff trust me i was in your same boat not too long ago Weight training Equine conformation Muscle Exercise Osteoarthritis Swimming Decompression sickness Urinary incontinence Bodybuilding Coronary heart disease Carpal tunnel syndrome First aid Non-Hodgkin's lymphoma Psoriasis Group A streptococcal infection Inflammation Atherosclerosis Breastfeeding Chronic fatigue syndrome Cramp Massage Asthma Fecal incontinence Autoimmune diseases Gout Menstrual cup Marathon (sport) Traumatic brain injury Wound healing phases Glucocorticoid Rheumatoid arthritis Aortic dissection Myocardial infarction Prostate cancer Stroke Replacement joint Diazepam Tai Chi Chuan Tyrannosaurus rex Childbirth Bruise Lung Common cold Aikido 